svn path=/trunk/koffice/; revision=294388

Back to 4 tiles in one pixmap; optimized the bigendian code a little.
(From Patrick's mail:
The reason why the pixmap is twice the value of RENDER_WIDTH and RENDER_HEIGHT
is to try to draw tiles 4x4.

I.e. if you look at the big endian code, doing m_pixmap = img results in a new
pixamp everytime.

doing m_pixmap.convertFromImage(img); will use the existing pixmap.  However,
here, the problem is that you also need to check so that it falls on a 4x4
tile boundary.)

svn path=/trunk/koffice/; revision=279306

Split application .desktop file and part .desktop file.
This allows
* more robust startup code, since it won't depend on where distributions or
users put their .desktop files in the K menu, or the local user config.
* more fine-grained preference handling.

For reference, here's what I did (with a partially-automated script) :
 1) add kde_services_DATA = kwordpart.desktop to Makefile.am
 2) cp kword.desktop kwordpart.desktop
 3) vi kword.desktop, put all mimetypes in MimeTypes, delete ServiceTypes and X-KDE-Library
   copy MimeType, for the file below:
 4) vi kwordpart.desktop, change Name, only keep Encoding/Type=Service/X-KDE-Library/X-KDE-NativeMimeType/MimeType/ServiceTypes
